HEADWORD: Glaucodot
<hw>Glau"co*dot</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>glayko`s</grk> silvery, gray + <grk>dido`nai</grk> to give.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A metallic mineral having a grayish tin-white
color, and containing cobalt and iron, with sulphur and
arsenic.</def>⟦br⟧
